emission is not correlated.

00:19:53.470 --> 00:19:57.410
You have many, many atoms,
but they are not synchronized.

00:19:57.410 --> 00:20:00.020
They are emitting randomly.

00:20:00.020 --> 00:20:03.180
So basically, you
have some finite--

00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:06.430
there are wave train.

00:20:06.430 --> 00:20:09.690
So in that wave train, you
get basically coherent.

00:20:09.690 --> 00:20:12.620
But you have many, many of
them with the random phase.

00:20:12.620 --> 00:20:14.490
That's why you
add them together,

00:20:14.490 --> 00:20:15.870
then you get incoherent.

00:20:15.870 --> 00:20:18.370
So coherent length
is essentially

00:20:18.370 --> 00:20:21.910
what is the length of
a finite wave train

00:20:21.910 --> 00:20:25.120
that you can define
deterministic phase.

00:20:25.120 --> 00:20:28.870
So d1-- so in just imagine
the Michelson interferometer,

00:20:28.870 --> 00:20:33.160
you have the optical
path first, d1 minus d2.

00:20:33.160 --> 00:20:37.760
But that difference is
within the distance,

00:20:37.760 --> 00:20:40.270
then you get interference.

00:20:40.270 --> 00:20:42.540
That's why you call the
coherence length and coherence

00:20:42.540 --> 00:20:44.290
time.

00:20:44.290 --> 00:20:49.540
And yeah, essentially,
that's it.

00:20:49.540 --> 00:20:52.680
So remember that if we had--

