00:21:59.880 --> 00:22:02.610
Another way to think
of spatially incoherent

00:22:02.610 --> 00:22:06.150
is you have many, many
plane waves propagating

00:22:06.150 --> 00:22:10.140
all the different directions,
but they are randomly--

00:22:10.140 --> 00:22:12.060
they have random initial phase.

00:22:12.060 --> 00:22:16.570
So especially in coherent
light, you cannot really define

00:22:16.570 --> 00:22:19.620
a unique propagation direction.

00:22:19.620 --> 00:22:21.870
But spatially
coherent light, you

00:22:21.870 --> 00:22:24.090
can always define direction.

