00:30:07.610 --> 00:30:11.560
and also temporally coherent.

00:30:11.560 --> 00:30:15.670
So the input field just
right after the input

00:30:15.670 --> 00:30:20.560
transparency is going to be just
a product of the illumination

00:30:20.560 --> 00:30:24.010
field and the
complex transparency.

00:30:24.010 --> 00:30:25.990
That's the input field.

00:30:25.990 --> 00:30:29.260
And you're going to take
the Fourier transform to get

00:30:29.260 --> 00:30:31.030
the field at the wave plane.

00:30:31.030 --> 00:30:35.090
And another Fourier transform,
you get the final image.

00:30:35.090 --> 00:30:38.890
And from that, we all know
that amplitude [INAUDIBLE]

00:30:38.890 --> 00:30:43.690
function is nothing but
the [INAUDIBLE] function

